12/05/2011
BISHKEK, Kyrgyzstan -- A Turkish journalist wanted by Ankara for alleged ties to a terror group has been arrested in Kyrgyzstan, the Kyrgyz National Committee confirmed on Wednesday (May 11th). 
Ali Osman Zor, 43, was detained on May 2nd, the committee told Radio Free Europe. 
Zor is wanted in Turkey for alleged links with a group connected to al-Qaeda. 
The journalist arrived in Kyrgyzstan nine months ago and has applied for political asylum there. 
(Hurriyet - 12/05/11; Radio Free Europe - 11/05/11)
